<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>So I guess an enchanter makes thease items. If so what do I have to do for him to make them?</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Your Answer My Son</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-01 12:14:50</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Two words. ORAL COPULATION</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: terraborn</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-23 08:55:18</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Simply pay him a "reasonable" price.  Do not ask "If I give you them gem, can you make me a *****".  That is like going to a restraunt and asking the Chef, I I give you a steak, will you cook it.  PPL make jewelry for profit, a modest portion of that profit is to compensate for the failure reat, that "all" have, even those with a 200 skill lvl. Consider the cost / rarity of the gem when looking to see if the price is fair.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Angelsyn Whitewings</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-14 01:20:15</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Well...<BR>
<BR>
     It takes about a skill of 60 or so to be reasonably sure you can make this item... it also takes a gem that's going to cost the enchanter at least 85pp or so to buy.<BR>
     And that's not counting the cost of all the gems he or she has bought in the past and lost because they failed to become items.<BR>
     Plus the trouble of going to Neriak to get the spells needed to enchant metal in the first place, which isn't always a safe run.<BR>
<BR>
     If you want this item and know an enchanter you can reasonably trust, buy the Fire Emerald yourself... and a bar of silver, just to be safe, and take it to them.  Ask nicely, but don't expect a guarantee for it to work.<BR>
     You might also give them a few plat for the time, and don't do it while they're hunting.<BR>
<BR>
     Or, if you're on the Xegony server, give me a couple of weeks to improve my skill and bring the gem to me.  I've only got a 45 right now, but I'm working on it.<BR>
<BR>
Angelsyn Whitewings<BR>
Cleric of twenty seasons.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
